.

Color pattern in UV light consisting of moderately broad, opisthocyrt, somewhat irregular dark bands, roughly paralleling growth lines; irregular pattern of light dots on primary and secondary spiral cords (see
Caze et al . 2010
).

Discussion. This species displays some variability in sculpture concerning the presence of the t spiral cord and the strength and number (1–3) of secondary spiral cords on the sutural ramp. In some specimens, B and C spiral cords weaken distinctly on last whorls equaling secondary cords. The protoconch is not preserved in the Paratethyan material studied, but based on specimens from the lower Piacenzian upper Pliocene Estepona Basin of southern Spain it consists of two smooth whorls (
Landau et al . 2004: 16
)

Paleoenvironment. The species seems to have preferred shallow marine, inner neritic and lagoonal environments, partly with sea grass meadows (e.g. Gainfarn, Steinebrunn) (
Zuschin et al. 2007
).

